## Key Conventions

### Code Style

- {{CONVENTION_1}}
- {{CONVENTION_2}}
- {{CONVENTION_3}}
- Every function that can fail returns an explicit error, not an exception
- Tests live next to the code they test, or mirror the src/ directory structure
- No magic numbers. Named constants or config values only.

### Git Conventions

- Branch naming: `feature/short-description`, `fix/short-description`, `chore/short-description`
- Commit messages: imperative mood, 50 chars max for subject line
- One logical change per commit. Atomic commits that pass tests independently.
- VERSION file uses 4-digit semver: `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH.MICRO`

### File Naming

- Source files: `kebab-case.ts` or `camelCase.ts` (pick one, be consistent)
- Test files: `{source-file}.test.ts`
- Config files: root directory, dotfile or `*.config.ts`

