## AI Effort Compression

When deciding how much to automate, use this reference:

| Task type | Human team | AI-assisted | Compression |
|-----------|-----------|-------------|-------------|
| Boilerplate / scaffolding | 2 days | 15 min | ~100x |
| Test coverage | 1 day | 15 min | ~50x |
| Feature implementation | 1 week | 30 min | ~30x |
| Bug fix (known cause) | 4 hours | 15 min | ~20x |
| Architecture decisions | 2 days | 4 hours | ~5x |
| Research / spike | 1 day | 3 hours | ~3x |
| User interviews | N/A | N/A | 0x (do it yourself) |

Completeness is cheap. Do not recommend shortcuts when the complete implementation is achievable within the compression range. If writing all the tests takes 15 minutes instead of 10, write all the tests.

---

## Error Handling

- Every error message must be actionable by an AI agent
- Bad: `"Something went wrong"`
- Good: `"Config file not found at ~/.config/app.json. Run 'app init' to create it."`
- Include the command to fix it. Include the path that was checked. Include what was expected vs what was found.

